{"nodes": [{"id": "backend_claude_md_prisma7_adapter", "label": "Prisma 7 PrismaPg Adapter Pattern", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Prisma 7 removed the url field from the datasource block; the connection is wired at runtime via new PrismaPg({connectionString: process.env.DATABASE_URL}) passed to super({adapter}) in PrismaService.", "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "backend_claude_md_tsbuildinfo_rationale", "label": "tsBuildInfoFile Placement Inside dist/", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "nest start --watch deletes dist/ on startup (deleteOutDir:true). A tsbuildinfo stored outside dist/ survives the wipe and tells tsc the build is current, so tsc emits nothing and the server crashes with 'Cannot find module dist\\main'. Keeping tsbuildinfo inside dist/ makes both get wiped together.", "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "backend_claude_md_jwtauthguard", "label": "Global JwtAuthGuard", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Applied globally in main.ts so every route is protected by default; @Public() is the explicit opt-out mechanism for public endpoints.", "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "backend_claude_md_public_decorator", "label": "@Public() Decorator", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "backend_claude_md_issuetokens", "label": "issueTokens(userId, email)", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Private method that signs both access (15min/JWT_SECRET) and refresh (7d/JWT_REFRESH_SECRET, carries jti) tokens together, keeping issuance atomic.", "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "backend_claude_md_refreshtoken_table", "label": "RefreshToken Table (bcrypt hash, jti-keyed)", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Refresh token is never in the request/response body; set as httpOnly;SameSite=Lax cookie jt_refresh scoped to /auth, and stored server-side as a bcrypt hash keyed by jti (separate table, not a column on User). Old row deleted and new pair issued on every refresh.", "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "backend_claude_md_currentuser_decorator", "label": "@CurrentUser() Decorator", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "backend_claude_md_jwtstrategy", "label": "JwtStrategy.validate()", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "backend_claude_md_oauth_flow", "label": "OAuth Login Flow (Google/GitHub)", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "GET /auth/google -> provider -> callback -> GoogleStrategy.validate() -> handleOAuthUser() -> issueTokens() -> storeOAuthCode() -> redirect with a short-lived code instead of tokens in the URL, so tokens are never exposed in the redirect.", "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "backend_claude_md_handleoauthuser", "label": "handleOAuthUser() Resolution", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Resolution order: (1) find existing Account by [provider, providerAccountId], (2) find User by email and link new Account, (3) create new User+Account \u2014 prevents duplicate accounts across providers.", "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "backend_claude_md_storeoauthcode", "label": "storeOAuthCode() Redis Exchange-Code Store", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Stores the issued token pair under a short-lived UUID in Redis (60s TTL) instead of putting tokens in the OAuth redirect URL; frontend exchanges the code via POST /auth/exchange-code.", "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "backend_claude_md_jobs_authorization_pattern", "label": "Jobs Ownership Check (findOne)", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Every service method operating on a specific job calls findOne(userId, jobId) first, which throws ForbiddenException if the job belongs to a different user \u2014 never skipped.", "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "backend_claude_md_job_event_logging", "label": "Job Event Logging (CREATED/STATUS_CHANGE)", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Events are written inside the same Prisma operation as the job mutation, never a separate call \u2014 a CREATED event on create, a STATUS_CHANGE event (fromStatus/toStatus) whenever PATCH /jobs/:id changes status.", "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "backend_claude_md_js_import_convention", "label": ".js Extension Import Convention", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "All source imports use .js extensions even though files are .ts (ESM-style paths); jest-e2e.json's moduleNameMapper strips .js so ts-jest can resolve them.", "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "backend_claude_md_storage_dual_driver", "label": "Storage Dual-Driver Pattern", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Global StorageModule exposes one STORAGE_SERVICE injection token backed by either LocalStorageService (dev) or OracleStorageService (prod), selected at startup by STORAGE_DRIVER.", "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "backend_claude_md_localstorageservice", "label": "LocalStorageService", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "backend_claude_md_oraclestorageservice", "label": "OracleStorageService", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "backend_claude_md_resumes_file_endpoint", "label": "GET /jobs/resumes/file Endpoint", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "backend_claude_md_resumes_presigned_url", "label": "GET /jobs/:jobId/resumes/url Presigned URL", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "backend_claude_md_resumes_upload_consistency", "label": "Resumes Upload Consistency (storage-first ordering)", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "ResumesService.upload writes to storage before the DB upsert; if the DB fails, the catch block deletes the uploaded file. A dangling storage file is judged safer than a DB record pointing at nothing. The old storage key is deleted only after the DB upsert succeeds.", "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "backend_claude_md_jobsservice_remove", "label": "JobsService.remove Resume Cleanup", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "When a job is deleted, JobsService.remove looks up the resume's storageKey before calling deleteMany, then fires a fire-and-forget storage delete; the Resume row itself is cleaned up by cascade.", "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "backend_claude_md_globalexceptionfilter", "label": "GlobalExceptionFilter (P2002->409, P2025->404)", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Catches Prisma P2002 (unique violation) -> 409 and P2025 (not found) -> 404; passes NestJS HttpException subclasses through unchanged; plain Error objects fall through to a 500 catch-all, so built-in exceptions must be thrown instead.", "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "backend_claude_md_nestjspino_logging", "label": "nestjs-pino Logging + Field Redaction", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "backend_claude_md_e2e_tests", "label": "Backend E2E Tests (live dev DB)", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Tests run against the live dev database with no mocking; each run uses a unique timestamped email, afterAll deletes that user (cascades). beforeAll manually mirrors main.ts's global pipes/guards/filters, so changes to main.ts must be mirrored in test setup.", "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}], "edges": [{"source": "backend_claude_md_handleoauthuser", "target": "backend_claude_md_issuetokens", "relation": "calls", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "backend_claude_md_issuetokens", "target": "backend_claude_md_storeoauthcode", "relation": "calls", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "backend_claude_md_oauth_flow", "target": "backend_claude_md_handleoauthuser", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "backend_claude_md_oauth_flow", "target": "backend_claude_md_storeoauthcode", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "backend_claude_md_oauth_flow", "target": "backend_claude_md_refreshtoken_table", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "backend_claude_md_localstorageservice", "target": "backend_claude_md_storage_dual_driver", "relation": "implements", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "backend_claude_md_oraclestorageservice", "target": "backend_claude_md_storage_dual_driver", "relation": "implements", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "backend_claude_md_resumes_file_endpoint", "target": "backend_claude_md_localstorageservice", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "backend_claude_md_resumes_presigned_url", "target": "backend_claude_md_oraclestorageservice", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "backend_claude_md_resumes_upload_consistency", "target": "backend_claude_md_storage_dual_driver", "relation": "references", "confidence": "INFERRED", "confidence_score": 0.85, "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "backend_claude_md_jobsservice_remove", "target": "backend_claude_md_resumes_upload_consistency", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "backend_claude_md_refreshtoken_table", "target": "frontend_claude_md_tokenstorage", "relation": "shares_data_with", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "backend_claude_md_jwtauthguard", "target": "frontend_claude_md_proxy_ts", "relation": "semantically_similar_to", "confidence": "INFERRED", "confidence_score": 0.85, "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "backend_claude_md_oauth_flow", "target": "frontend_claude_md_setauth", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "INFERRED", "confidence_score": 0.75, "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "backend_claude_md_oauth_flow", "target": "frontend_claude_md_axios_instance", "relation": "references", "confidence": "AMBIGUOUS", "confidence_score": 0.25, "source_file": "backend/CLAUDE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}], "hyperedges": [{"id": "storage_driver_selection_pattern", "label": "Storage Driver Selection Pattern", "nodes": ["backend_claude_md_storage_dual_driver", "backend_claude_md_localstorageservice", "backend_claude_md_oraclestorageservice", "backend_claude_md_resumes_file_endpoint", "backend_claude_md_resumes_presigned_url"], "relation": "implement", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 0.9, "source_file